Program: Discovery
Title: Volcanic crisis in Montserrat
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwqh
Last Broadcast Date: 16 September 1996
Volcanic crisis in Montserrat in the Caribbean. The volcano woke up after 400 years dormant, plunging the island into crisis. Also in the programme, the anti-cancer drug that gets its inspiration from a tropical sea sponge and the exertions of making a noise. Presenter: Andrew Luck-Baker.